node.text:
People ask me all the time how I’m always so motivated and inspired…

I’M NOT!!

I honestly never wanted to work 80+ hrs a week in the kitchen, I didn’t want to put myself OUT THERE on the internet and make all these recipe videos, and I still don’t want to go the gym every single day.

And to tell you the truth, I really didn’t want to post this video either.

“Who the fck am I to say these things?”
“Just stick to your recipes…”
“Ain’t nobody wanna hear this”
“Shoot it again cuz message wack!!”

These are the thoughts before posting. 

If I waited for the perfect moment when I felt good and comfortable about it, I be laying in the couch watching kdrama and scratching my balls. Ya mean?? 🙃

But yo…

There might be one or two people who might need this message.

If that’s you, I hope you take the action  needed to get you closer to your goals.

Sometimes… actually MOST OF THE TIMES I ain’t inspired or motivated to do things. But I feel inspired & motivated AFTER taking the action.

So go do yourself a favor and take an imperfect action today. Even if it’s a small baby step. Promise you it’ll make you feel better.

Hope you’re having a blessed day!!

Send y’all nothing but good energy~

Peace & Sarang ✌🏻❤️

“You just need few friends who will love you for who you are.” #MotivationalMonday

I spoke on an event yesterday virtually and they asked what’s your message to 14-18 year old ME…

And my message to the young 14-18 year olds is to keep good friend around who will LOVE YOU & ACCEPT YOU FOR WHO YOU ARE.

If you have a core circle of friend who love you for who you are, you’ll have the confidence to be YOU even if the world don’t accept you for who you are.

And I thank these guys for allowing me to be me and accepting me for who I am. 🙏🏼

Shoutout to wifeys for allowing us to be boyz and talk about our crazy stories while we soju it up all night~

Can’t wait to camp with our kids in the future… 79s FOR LIFE!! 🙏🏼❤️
